APC Chairman in Enugu State,Ugochukwu Agballah yesterday restated his determination to end years of PDP Cartel in political calculation of the coal city, Enugu. Barr.Agballah made the pronouncement in his homestead,Udi while addressing party supporters who had gathered to wish him well in his new assignment as Enugu State prepares to hold Local Government and Councillorship Election . According to Agballah whose father, late Chief Petrus Agballah was the Minority Leader in the old Anambra State under Jim Nwobodo’s administration in the Second Republic Ebonyi Deputy Speaker, Odefa Reaffirms His Membership Of PDP 2023: PDP Will Return To Power, Ayu Assures The new APC Chairman who was impressed by the solidarity accorded him so far by party faithful in the state disclosed that though PDP had planned to rig the Wednesday election, but warned that his party would do everything possible to protect the votes of its Local Government and Councillorship Candidates. Osita Eze,an indigene of Udi-Town and Personal Assistant to Minister for Foreign Affairs, Chief Geoffrey Onyeama who addressed the crowd at the occasion said that APC was working very hard to break PDP monopoly in Enugu State politics and boasted that the party was ever ready to win the present and future political offices in the State. He advised party faithful to always support APC in their quest to wrestle power from PDP in the State. the state. APC stakeholder in the state,Dr.Patrick Neboh in a speech described the new APC Chairman in the state as a dogged fighter and grassroots politician who is determined to make his people proud if given the opportunity and urged the people of Udi/Agbudu Ward to support the party’s candidates in the present and future elections in Enugu State.